SIMPLE: pensioner
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pensioner
<hw>Pen"sion*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One in
receipt of a pension; hence, figuratively, a dependent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fickle <qex>pensioners</qex> of Morpheus' train.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old <qex>pensioners</qex> . . . of Chelsea Hospital.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of an honorable band of gentlemen who attend the
sovereign of England on state occasions, and receive an annual pension,
or allowance, of ⟦pound⟧150 and two horses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>pensionnaire</ets> one who pays for his
board. Cf. <er>Pensionary</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>In the
university of Cambridge, England, one who pays for his living in
commons; -- corresponding to <simto>commoner</simto> at Oxford.</def>
<rj><au>Ld. Lytton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pensive</ent>⟦br⟧
